		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <Blockquote>
<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/036020.html">ABASHI: WTH is up with the Shaman befriend animal spell?</a><P>

We get this spell at 29 and it now has a lock so you cant charm anything higher than 26??? PLEASE EXPLAIN HOW THIS CAN BE USEFUL????? AND WHY IT WAS DONE?<P>

<B>With levels going above 50, we had to put in code to catch caps that were controlled by the level ceiling before. One of these was a safety net for charm, which caught this spell. Assuming that they don't have it already (my spell list is dated), we'll be giving Shaman the higher level animal charm spell with a higher cap.<P> 

I apologize for this not being in the patch message.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/037657.html">Ashame wolf form was a nerf no role playing i got attack by cross treewind</a><P>

I got attacked by cross treewind when in dog form and holly scowls ready to attack. Didn't they say if a wild dog was in the city wouldn't you kill it? Well how do they explain the defenders of wolves and bears attackin me? Bah just a plain old nerf we shoulda kept the same faction in wolf form as in normal form or be the same as a wolf.<P>

<B>I mentioned in another thread that Cros and Holly shouldn't be attacking druids in wolfform just by virtue of them being a wolf. I've forwarded this to the faction guy to look into it.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/038033.html">OMG! Necros get exp rez??</a><P>

I just found this out... i may be a little late, yeah, but wtf? give me a BREAK!<P>

<B>These spells are balanced. I think that once people have an idea how they work, they'll pretty much agree. Until then however I'll leave you to debate them :)<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<I>Rumor has it that this experience res costs a major regeant...the necromancers life.</I><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/038076.html">Aradune/Smed: Please Help...</a><P>

I still have not received my Kunark CD.<P>

<B>SambusV, please send me (<a href="mailto:gwrinn@verant.com">gwrinn@verant.com</a>) your station name and shipping address. I'll see what I can find out.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/038210.html">Reasons for enchanters to get a spectre illusion.</a><P>

Before, the excuse was used that enchanters couldn't get any more illusions b/c it would take too much memory to add another file to the global index. This spectre image has been added to the global file, and there is no reason not to give this to us.<P>

<B>I think I might have mentioned this in the other thread, but the spectre model has too many poly's to have two classes able to create spectres on demand. System resources are unfortunately finite, and we have to keep EQ usable by people with Voodoo1 cards.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/038425.html">Manaskin spell bugged!</a><P>

My friends complained about manaskin not having any noticeable mana regeneration effect. Being the gnome that I am, I asked them to do a little test for me.<P>

<B>It's not bugged. Manaskin only adds a very small amount to the mana-regen rate. The resolution of each "chunk" of mana that displays when medding is probably too large to show the additional 10 mana/minute that this spell grants.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

it is 2mana/tick or 20mana/min. Not a lot at all, but still a decent gimme for a diamondskin upgrade that uses the same component.<P>

<B>Hmmm, maybe GZ improved it. I'll chat with him when I see him next. In any case, it's certianly not meant to be a substitute for clarity.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/038683.html">Hey Brad, here's one for ya!</a><P>

If Bards and actors and Rogues are cunning, why can't they both have Feign Death? Chances are they won't get FD and I'm sure there are many reasons against it but, it's just a question.<P>

<B>Well, I suppose pretending that you are someone else and convincingly pretending you are dead are two different things.<P>

Really though, we didn't want to hand out Feign Death to everyone, and not everyone can have every skill, even when it's cool and incredibly useful (especially when it's cool and incredibly useful). When we started looking for a way for rogues to reduce their "hate" value, feign death was an option but we thought it would be cheesy to just duplicate another skill. That's how we came up with Evade.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/038758.html">This is not a complaint. Honest question about shotting arrows.</a><P>

I’m curious about the message “Your target is above or below you” when attempting to plink arrows at a nasty.<P>

<B>Shots with projectile weapons are allowed or disallowed based upon the delta-Z (Difference in the value of the Z-coordinant) of your feet versus the creatures feet. It was primarily done to disallow some exploits that are possible in the event that there is no control. The downside is that if you are standing on a hill, and for instance a sand giant is at the bottom of a hill, you might not be able to fire at it even if it is at eyelevel with you. <P>

We could look into increasing the maximum allowable delta-z if that would be helpful.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/038787.html">Plans for more content? NOT A RANT!</a><P>

Are there plans in the works to add more content to the zones other than Kunark to "mesh" the old world with the new? For example, an NPC in Neriak that wants you to get something from a zone in Kunark, or a quest from someone in Overthere Outpost asking for supplies from "home".<P>

<B>We are constantly planning an implementing more content, quests, items, etc. There are already many quests in that "link" the two continents. I've heard that there's even an Iksar prisoner in one of the old dungeons :)<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/038789.html">Pickpocket.. Ninja looting?</a><P>

Just wondering if you can pickpocket something that someone else is fighting?<P>
 
<B>Yes.</B><P>

And if you can would that not be about a the same as Ninja looting, except you do it before the creature is dead.<P> 

<B>Not really, the ninjalooting restriction primarily applies to special items. Since rogues can't PP anything but coin and the odd non-magical item, it's not really a major concern.</B><P> 

Oh one more thing is thier any way to tell if a rogue comes up and steals all the loot off of what your fighting... that is if he can?<P>

<B>If the critter scolds him perhaps :)<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

Please dont get me wrong. Just a question base on your answer. Is ninja looting only on those rare magic objects. Like if I was to loot a guard or a HG someone killed that would not be ninja looting, but if I looted a BBC off of the SK in befallen that someone kill that would be ninja looting.<P>
 
<B>Though we would expect people to volunatarily comply with the rule just out of common courtesy, we'll only be investigating the issues where it involves a special item or NPC. In other words, we're not going after the guy who accidently loots a hill giant out of turn, but the one who madly right-clicks the corpse while a lotto is going on, takes the items, and camps.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/038796.html">Gordon - No Exp from Blues?</a><P>

In Kanark for the last since I got my CD there are some BLUE cretures that will not give exp.<P>

Sanarks in Burning Woods come to mind.<P>

<B>This doesn't sound intentional. Is there any other information that you can give that can help us track the issue down? Is anyone else having the same problem? It's possible that we might have an unaccounted-for overflow somewhere due to to the size of the numbers that we are working with now. Any additional information would help.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/038802.html">Left/Right on /y backwards?</a><P>

Don't know if this has been addressed, but when using /y, the people around you don't get the right information. The ahead/behind is correct, but XXX yells for help from in front and to the left of you. You know what I do? I turn right, cause that's where he is.<P>

<B>Is this always the case? Strange we didn't notice it before. I'll send it to the client guy.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/038808.html">Abashi? You on? Where's my Kunark CD?!?!</a><P>

In 3 days, it will be a Month since I ordered the Expansion.
In 9 days, it will be a Month since you charged me for the Disc and NEXT - DAY service.<P>

<B>Email me (<a href="mailto:gwrinn@verant.com">gwrinn@verant.com</a>) your station name and shipping address. I'll see what I can find out.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/038832.html">Finding spells beyound 50</a><P>

I've yet to see anyone casting a spell past 50 they didn't buy at their vendor. In almost 3 weeks of playing, I've yet to hear of a single post 50 spell dropping off a mob. <P>

<B>I've got the EQLive team checking on this. I'll get back after I get the report from them. Just one note, Kunark has only been live for a week and a half :)<P> 

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/038833.html">A very simple fix to overcrowding and Kill stealing.</a><P>

A very simple way to fix this is increase the spawns. More often than not, I find that the people in my group have full mana and full health. The problem is, that we have nothing to do with this mana and health, because there are never enough mobs to kill.<P>

<B>Increasing spawns does not decrease overcrowding, it in fact encourages it. If we keep increasing spawns as more and more people enter the zone, sooner or later things are going to break because there's nothing to encourage people to leave the zone in search of more fruitful hunting ground.<P> 

We don't want to encourage people to jump on a never-ending hack-and-slash conveyor belt, we'd rather encourage them to explore.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/038839.html">Abashi Please read - My hard earned faction went from Amiable to Threatening!!!</a><P>

I play a Dark Elf Shadowknight, and with the hundreds if not THOUSANDS of Deathfist Orcs I've slain in pennace I had been able to raise my faction with the Ashen Order (the monk's in west Freeport) to the point where they were amiable to me.<P>
 
The day that Kunark went live my faction PLUMETTED from amiable to dubious.<P>

<B>This does indeed sound strange. Are you sure that you haven't done anything (quests, etc.) that would cause something like this? You seem to know your way around factions pretty well but I have to ask.<P>
 
Anyone else have anything like this happen recently?<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/038786.html">Group XP screwy?</a><P>

Last night in the City of Mist we were killing the Lord.
2+ groups totally about 16 people were fighting this thing. A loner paladin wanders by and joins the fray.<P>

He gets a solo kill from 16 other people!
That is sooo off-base its not even funny.<P>

And he did it with melee skills only since the Lord is 100% magic resistant, so GB help there.<P>

<B>There are some limited cases where something like this can happen due to the way the group aggregate damage system works. Due to the way everything interacts, changing the system further probably isn't feasible.<P>

On an opinionated note, it does seem like a bit of poetic justice to hear about melee types accidently KS'ing from casters :)<P>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
